<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8989b: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)<note n="39" xml:id="d716fn39">The
                                        same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, to the
                                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom as telegram No. 145,
                                        February 24, 6 p.m.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-24T17:00:00-05:00">February 24, 1939—5 p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>111. I would like to have your report as to what extent the
                                    French Government consider that Franco will refrain from
                                    executions on the basis of reprisals.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>